The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
Inside the while loop the condition is 'while (MHD_RO_END != (ro = va_arg(ap, enum MHD_ResponseOptions)))', so the loop body is executed only when ro != MHD_RO_END. Therefore the switch case 'case MHD_RO_END:' inside that body can never be reached (dead code). This is a direct violation of MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.1 (unreachable code).
